## 4. What ChatGPT via MCP Should Do in This Platform

This is the most important section because it defines the business purpose of the integration.

ChatGPT via MCP should serve as the platform’s **admin-only document generation assistant**.

## 4.1 Primary responsibilities

| Capability | What it should do |
|---|---|
| **Template-based document generation** | draft structured documents such as policies, SOPs, implementation guides, operational documents, partner resources, and member-facing templates |
| **Document transformation** | turn notes, uploaded files, meeting summaries, forms, or outlines into structured draft documents |
| **Context-aware drafting** | use suite context, document type, service type, member tier, and business rules provided by MCP tools |
| **Metadata generation** | generate title, summary, tags, slug, SEO title, SEO description, and audience suggestions |
| **Draft revision** | rewrite sections for clarity, brevity, tone, structure, or audience |
| **Reference-aware drafting** | search and fetch internal reference documents via MCP tools before composing output |
| **Operational support output** | draft service-response documents, action plans, implementation notes, discovery outputs, and internal operating docs |

## 4.2 What it should not do

| Capability | Why it should not do it |
|---|---|
| publish content directly | publishing must remain an app-controlled admin action |
| grant access or entitlements | access remains controlled by Firebase + Firestore business state |
| bypass admin review | generated content must be reviewed |
| write to arbitrary application records without guardrails | write actions are high risk and should be tightly scoped or avoided initially |
| replace Gemini’s lightweight role | that would create overlap and unnecessary complexity |

## 4.3 Recommended first-phase workflows

| Workflow | Trigger | Output |
|---|---|---|
| Generate draft from template | admin selects template and context | structured draft document |
| Generate from uploaded source | admin uploads notes or a source file | first-pass draft |
| Suggest metadata | admin requests title, tags, SEO | structured metadata output |
| Revise draft | admin selects existing text | improved version |
| Create suite overview | admin selects suite | suite-level overview text |

## 4.4 Recommended later-phase workflows

- transform meeting notes into implementation documents
- generate discovery-call summaries and action plans
- convert internal guidance into member-facing versions
- create multi-document packs based on template bundles
- generate draft responses for service request workflows

