## 5. Why MCP Is the Right Pattern for This App

MCP is the right architecture because the model needs access to **business-specific tools and context** without hardcoding all that logic directly into prompts.

### Why not plain prompt-only generation

Because this platform has:

- documentation suites
- document types
- internal templates
- service request context
- business rules
- reference content
- structured metadata requirements

Trying to stuff all of that into a single giant prompt would produce a fragile little monster.

### Why MCP fits

A remote MCP server lets the model use **tools** such as:

- search for relevant internal references
- fetch document templates
- fetch suite rules
- fetch content-type requirements
- generate or revise structured content under controlled rules

That gives you a cleaner separation between:

- **OpenAI model reasoning and generation**
- **application-specific business tools**
- **application-controlled review and storage**

---

## 6. Recommended Architecture

The cleanest architecture for this application is:

`Admin UI -> App Backend -> OpenAI Responses API -> Remote MCP Server -> Firestore / reference services -> App Backend -> Firestore -> Admin Review`

## 6.1 Core components

| Component | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| **Admin UI** | collects template choice, source material, generation instructions, and displays results |
| **Next.js backend** | validates admin access, orchestrates requests, stores jobs and versions |
| **OpenAI Responses API** | runs the model with MCP tools enabled |
| **Remote MCP server** | exposes controlled business tools to the model |
| **Firestore** | stores templates, documents, jobs, results, and logs |
| **Cloudflare** | fronts the main app and can protect API ingress |
| **Gemini** | continues to handle lightweight assistive tasks separately |

## 6.2 Preferred operating pattern

Use the **application backend** as the caller of the OpenAI API.

### Why

- better security
- easier audit logging
- easier role enforcement
- easier environment management
- easier to attach application context and Firestore IDs

### Do not do this initially

Do not put the OpenAI call directly in the browser. That would be a needlessly creative way to leak secrets and lose control.

