## 10. MCP Server Scope and Tool Design

The MCP server should start narrow.

## 10.1 Minimum useful toolset

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `list_document_templates` | list available templates |
| `get_document_template` | return full template structure and rules |
| `get_suite_context` | return documentation suite context |
| `get_content_type_rules` | return document-type requirements |
| `search_reference_content` | find supporting content |
| `fetch_reference_content` | return the selected reference content |
| `suggest_document_metadata` | generate title, summary, tags, slug |
| `create_document_outline` | return a structured outline |
| `revise_document_section` | rewrite a specific section |

## 10.2 Recommended optional tools after MVP

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `create_document_draft` | server-side business wrapper around generation if needed |
| `generate_service_response` | document outputs for service workflows |
| `list_style_guides` | retrieve editorial or brand guidance |
| `fetch_prompt_policy` | retrieve policy-controlled generation instructions |

## 10.3 Connector-compatible tools

If you also want the server to work cleanly with ChatGPT connectors or deep research, implement at least:

- `search`
- `fetch`

These are the most portable tool shapes for generalized retrieval workflows.

---

## 11. Recommended Tool Governance

Not all tools should be available in all workflows.

## 11.1 Per-workflow tool restrictions

| Workflow | Allowed tools |
|---|---|
| metadata suggestion | `get_document_template`, `get_suite_context`, `suggest_document_metadata` |
| outline generation | `get_document_template`, `get_content_type_rules`, `search_reference_content`, `fetch_reference_content`, `create_document_outline` |
| section revision | `revise_document_section` plus retrieval tools if needed |
| manual ChatGPT Developer Mode testing | broader tool set, but still not full write access |

## 11.2 Rule

Always restrict `allowed_tools` as tightly as possible per request.

This reduces:

- accidental overreach
- irrelevant tool calls
- security exposure
- prompt-injection blast radius

