## 13. Recommended Deployment Architecture

## 13.1 Main application

Your web application remains where it is today, fronted by Cloudflare.

## 13.2 MCP server

Deploy the MCP server as a separate service.

### Recommended hosting options

| Option | Why it may fit |
|---|---|
| **Cloudflare Workers / Containers** | consistent with your existing Cloudflare setup if supported by your MCP framework |
| **Node service on your current infrastructure** | simple if you already operate Node backends |
| **Cloud Run or equivalent** | clean separation and scalable stateless service |

## 13.3 Recommendation

Use a dedicated server or service boundary for MCP rather than embedding it directly inside the main Next.js runtime.

### Why

- cleaner scaling
- better security boundary
- easier auth handling
- easier tooling version control
- easier to test independently

