## 20. Operational Workflow Examples

## 20.1 Generate a document from a template

1. admin opens the document-generation form
2. admin selects a template
3. admin enters title, audience, purpose, and optional notes
4. backend validates template and admin permissions
5. backend creates a generation job record
6. backend calls the Responses API with the MCP server attached
7. model uses tools such as:
   - `get_document_template`
   - `get_suite_context`
   - `search_reference_content`
   - `fetch_reference_content`
8. model returns a structured draft
9. backend stores version 1
10. admin reviews and edits
11. final draft is saved to the target document record

## 20.2 Suggest metadata for an uploaded document

1. admin uploads a document
2. app extracts or normalizes document text
3. backend creates a metadata job
4. backend enables only metadata-safe tools
5. model returns title, summary, tags, slug, and SEO fields
6. admin accepts or edits them
7. final metadata is saved

## 20.3 Revise an existing section

1. admin selects a section of text
2. admin chooses a revision instruction such as simplify, shorten, or adapt for executive audience
3. backend sends the current text and relevant context
4. model returns revised text only
5. admin accepts, edits, or rejects

