## 23. Error Handling and Fallback Design

The system must degrade gracefully.

## 23.1 Likely failure modes

| Failure mode | Required handling |
|---|---|
| OpenAI API failure | log, show recoverable admin error |
| MCP server unavailable | log, show fallback/manual option |
| tool auth failure | fail cleanly, keep job record |
| invalid template | reject before model call |
| malformed model output | treat as failed generation |
| timeout | log timeout and allow retry |

## 23.2 Fallback rule

If generation fails:

- the admin UI remains usable
- manual entry remains available
- the failure is logged
- the job record remains visible for debugging

